HEADWORD: Malaxation
<hw>Mal`ax*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>malaxatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>malaxation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act
of softening by mixing with a thinner substance; the formation of
ingredients into a mass for pills or plasters.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

